President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama sent their warmest wishes to Muslim communities around the world on the occasion of Eid-al-Fitr. They recognized the importance of Ramadan as a time of fasting, prayer, and spiritual renewal for Muslims. They also highlighted the significance of serving the less fortunate during this time, emphasizing the obligations that people of all faiths have towards each other. The President acknowledged the contributions of Muslim Americans to the United States, stating that communities of faith, including Muslim Americans, enrich the nation's life, strengthen democracy, and uphold freedoms such as the freedom of religion. He expressed solidarity with people of all faiths in protecting and advancing this universal human right. The President concluded by congratulating Muslim Americans and Muslims worldwide on this joyous day, saying "Eid Mubarak."